    'name' => 'two_way_sync',
    'description' => 'Synchronize data between two SQLite databases (or a SQLite DB and a JSON API endpoint). Computes row-level differences using primary keys: identifies new rows (INSERT), changed rows (UPDATE), and missing rows (DELETE). Supports directional sync (A→B, B→A, or full bidirectional merge) with configurable conflict resolution (keep A, keep B, or keep newest by timestamp). The \'diff\' mode only reports differences without modifying data. First data synchronization capability in the ecosystem. Never throws — all errors returned as structured data.',
    'parameters' => 
